        "body": "## Summary\n\nHarden Signal approval reaction binding so native reaction targets are only attached to canonical OpenClaw approval prompts.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Require a canonical `ID: <approvalId>` header before Signal extracts approval reaction bindings from outbound text.\n- Require `/approve <approvalId> ...` command lines to match that header before reaction hints or targets are registered.\n- Add Signal regression coverage for copied approval-command snippets and mismatched prompt IDs.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-signal.config.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Notes\n\nBehavior addressed: Signal approval reactions now bind only to canonical approval prompts with matching IDs.\nReal environment tested: local checkout on branch `757`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-signal.config.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts --reporter=dot`.\nEvidence after fix: focused Signal approval-reaction suite passed with 18 tests.\nObserved result after fix: ordinary outbound snippets without canonical approval IDs do not append reaction hints or register reaction targets; canonical prompts remain covered by the existing target-mode reaction test.\nWhat was not tested: live Signal service delivery.\n",
